title: World Water Body Limits
name: World Water Body Limits
description:
This single polygon shapefile defines the limits (boundaries) of all of the world's tidal water bodies with dimensions larger than 100 km by 250 km, including the world's four oceans:  the Arctic, Atlantic, Indian, and Pacific.   The coastlines are rough schematic outlines; much more care is taken on the lines separating water bodies by name.

     Of course, other interpretations and names exist.  This dataset considers the so-called "Southern Ocean" to be an optional name recently adopted by and for hydrographers, and not to be one of the world's four oceans, as per the National Geographic Society (US) and other geographic authorities.  

     The shapefile attributes include water body names and define which ocean contains the various water bodies.  This dataset was updated in December 2010 but tends to need little or no modification over long periods of time.

     Users are encouraged to submit feedback, .shp, and/or .kml files;  contact the Office of the Geographer and Global Issues, Rm. 6510-INR/GGI/GIU, US Dept. of State, 2201 C St. NW, Washington, DC 20520.

author.source: Office of the Geographer of the U.S. Department of State
